	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=6&mid=99684840814995>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99684840814995>Leveling in Odus</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99684840814995#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 3rd 10:20 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=81145><span id= >Zuga</span></a><br><span id=notbold>82 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><br>This is a good guide - but there is another way for Erudite Paladin (or Cleric) to level.&nbsp;&nbsp;Between Toxx, the Warrens, and Kerra Island you have enough hunting grounds to stay on Odus through level 15.  And when the Stonebrunt Mts zone comes online you will probably be able to stay until level 30!<br><br>Level 1 - tough level but go fight in Toxx.  Kill everything you can.  Save money and sell items to buy sacks or backpacks. <br><br>Level 2-5 make the run to the Paineel newbie ground (zone into Paineel and take the first left). To make this run succesfully take a left when you leave Erudin and hug the wall all the way around to Paineel.  Beware of skeletons around the Paineel entrance.   The two skeleton guards in the tunnel should not aggro on you once you are second level. Remember to run straight down the middle of the tunnel as you exit into the Paineel newbie area or the skeleton guards will aggro on you and kill you.  See if you can get bound right there in the newbie zone.<br>  <br>Now kill as many decayed skeletons as you can - load up on the bone chips, don't leave until you don't have room for any more - then run back to Erudin and do the "Skeleton Killing" quest.  Talk to Lumi Stergnon in the Temple of Quellios and you will be given a box to use in your battle. Fill it with bone chips and combine it to get a box of bones. When you return it to the cleric you will get a LOT of exp, and sometimes first level cleric spells, and rawhide armor.  You will level fast and by level five you should have full suit of rawhide.<br><br>Level 6-7  you have two options - hunt kobolds in Toxx if you can't find anyone to group with, or hunt kobolds in Warrens if you are in a group.  You will level fast in the Warrens.  If hunting in Toxx keep an eye out for useless cloth caps that drop from kobold scouts -- if you find any hand them into the skeleton guards in the Paineel tunnel for a surprise. <br><br>Level 8 - 15 Warrens all the way baby!!!   Hand in molars to the Erudin in the Deepwater Knight courtyard and by level 10 you should have a suit of ringmail.  Hand in the weapons that drop and you will start building up a good supply of pp.   You can solo in the Warrens, but grouping is recommended.  <br><br>Level 16 - 17 Trade off between Kerra Island and the Warrens.  You start to level slower now.  You will want to do both of the Midnight armor quests to get your special Erudite Paladin/Cleric only armor.  Then you can leave the island.  Get a teleport to Butcherblock, get bound in Kaladim, and go fight in Unrest to practice your evocation skill against the Undead.  <br><br>Level 18(+)  Go see the world - but keep an eye on the Stonebrunt Mts.  If it turns out to be a decent zone then you can stay on Odus until level 30.  Good luck!!<br><br>PS - There is very little player auctioning going on in Erudin.  However my erudite paladin picked up lots of decent stuff just by examining all the merchants in Erudin on a regular basis.  Especially check out the jewelers in Erudin palace - I picked up some stat buffing jewelry which we SORELY need.  Also, once you have saved up a good amount of loot try and get a port to the Commonlands and buy a decent magical weapon.  (I got a Messenger of the Queen)<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
